commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye.
Level 2: used arraylist to store the entered text.
Add the ability to mark tasks as done and the ability to change the status back to not done. Include a task class to encapsulate the information.
Add support for tracking three types of tasks: ToDos, Events, Deadlines. Reform the structure of the code.
Test using the I/O redirection technique
commitResults.messageBody: Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
